# Implementation Plan - Rich Bare Acts Library & Complaint Form Integration

We will upgrade the **Baraat (Bare Act) Library** from a basic list of static cards into a premium, interactive **Bare Acts Explorer**. We will also integrate a legal API information panel to list available open-source APIs, and implement an **"Apply to Complaint"** flow that pre-fills the complaint form according to the chosen act/section.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Since public, CORS-enabled APIs for *all* Indian central and state laws do not exist for free without authorization keys (e.g., Indian Kanoon requires registration and payment for commercial queries), we will implement a dual-engine architecture:
> 1. A rich, high-fidelity local database of major Bare Acts (IPC, Consumer Protection Act, RTI, etc.) with chapters, sections, and descriptions that is fully searchable and responsive.
> 2. An **Open Source Legal API Dashboard** inside the library that showcases available APIs (Indian Kanoon, eCourts India, CivicTech GitHub datasets) with endpoint descriptions, and provides a mock request viewer demonstrating how developers can integrate them.
> Please review and confirm if this meets your requirements for "where are all api we can get".

